    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7</p><p>Chop the<strong>\u00a0potatoes </strong>(skins on) into rough bite-sized pieces</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>chopped potatoes</strong> to one side of a baking tray with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>meat-free\u00a0sausages</strong> to the other side of the tray and put the tray in the oven for an initial 18-20 min or until everything is almost cooked through</p><p>Tip: Cooking for 4? Use 2 trays!</p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst everything is cooking, combine the <strong>wholegrain mustard</strong> with the <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>mayo</strong>, <strong>red wine vinegar</strong>,\u00a01 tbsp <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tbsp]</span> <strong>olive oil</strong> and a pinch of <strong>pepper</strong> in a small bowl \u2013 this is your <strong>honey mustard dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Snap\u00a0the <strong>walnuts</strong> in half roughly</p><p>Peel and cut the <strong>red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into thin wedges, then separate into petals</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>After an initial 18-20 min, add the<strong> onion petals\u00a0</strong>to the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></p><p>Return the tray<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span> to the oven for a further 5 min or until the onion is starting to soften</p><p>Add the <strong>halved walnuts</strong> for a final 3-4 min or until\u00a0everything is cooked through and\u00a0the walnuts are toasted</p><p>Tip: Watch the walnuts like a hawk to make sure they don't burn!</p><p>Meanwhile, wash the<strong> shredded kale</strong> then pat dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Chop the\u00a0<strong>apple<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong>\u00a0into matchsticks</p><p>Once everything is cooked, add the<strong> shredded kale</strong>, <strong>apple matchsticks</strong>,\u00a0<strong>cooked potatoes</strong>,<strong> roasted onion petals</strong> and<strong> toasted walnuts</strong> to a large bowl</p><p>Add <strong>half</strong> of the <strong>honey mustard dressing</strong> (you'll use the rest later!) and gently mix together \u2013 this is your <strong>kale salad with honey mustard dressing</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/meat-free-sausage-and-kale-salad-with-honey-mustard-dressing/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>meat-free sausages</strong> over the <strong>kale salad</strong></p><p>Drizzle the <strong>remaining honey mustard dressing</strong> all over</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
